    "This representation is mapped to hyperbolic space using the exponential map, denoted as g(x) = exp 0 (f θ (x)).",
    "In many hyperbolic works, additional information about hierarchical relations between classes is assumed.",
    "Let H = (Y, P, R), with Y the class labels denoting the leaf nodes of the hierarchy, P the internal nodes, and R the set of hypernym-hyponym relations of the hierarchy.",
    "Below, we discuss how current literature tackles each strategy in detail sequentially.",
    "The most direct way to induce hyperbolic geometry in the classification space is by replacing the classification layer by a hyperbolic alternative."
